data.title: Delaware State Parks
data.meta_description: Cape Henlopen's beaches attract thousands of visitors who enjoy ocean swimming and sunbathing.
data.text:
Dolphin Watch

Tuesday, August 20, 2024

9:00 AM

Look for bottlenose dolphins from our shore overlook and find out why they swim within sight of our beaches. For ages 7 and older with an adult. Online registration ends 24 hours prior to the program. After that, please call 302-645-6852. $6 per person.

Register Online

For ages 7 and older with an adult. Online registration ends 24 hours prior to the program. After that, please call 302-645-6852. $6 per person. Cape Henlopen

Seining the Bay

Wednesday, August 21, 2024

9:00 AM

Fish the shallows of Delaware Bay using a beach seine net to collect fish, crabs and other creatures, and discover how the bay functions as a nursery. Dress to get wet and wear secure shoes, no flip-flops. For ages 5 and older with an adult. Online registration closes 24 hours prior to the program. After that please call 302-645-6852. $7 per person

8:30 AM

Tuesday, September 10, 2024

8:00 AM

Search the park for birds on their fall migration. Each walk will target current birding hot spots. For beginning and intermediate birders. Bring your binoculars or borrow a pair of ours. For ages 10 and older with an adult. Free, no registration required. Call 302-645-8983 for more information.

11:00 AM

Children's Fantasy Trail 2024

Friday, October 25, 2024

6:00 PM

Wear your Halloween costume and Trick-or-Treat for candy and toys with your favorite storybook characters along our jack-o-lantern lined trail. Entertainment under the tent each evening may include singing, juggling, magic and more. Events and details subject to change. $6 per person, adults and children. Call 302-645-8983 for more information.

11:00 AM
